Operators:-Operators are symbols which are used to perform operations in operands.

Arithmetic Operators:--

+   Addition       a+b
-   subtraction    a-b
*   Multiplication a*b
/   division       a/b
%   modulo         a%b 

Relational operators:relational operator are used to show relation between two operands.

>       greater than                                      a>b
<       less than                                         a<b
>=     greater than or equal to                           a>=b
<=      less than or equal to                             a<=b
==      equal(lose)(only checks value not type)           a==b
===     equal(strict)(checks type+value both)             a===b
!=      not equal to                                      a!=b
!==         not  losely equal                              a!==b
!===    not   strict equal                                 a!===b

Assignment operators (=):-

a=b;    //copies value of b to a
a+=b;   //a=a+b
a+=1;   //a=a+1
a-=b;   //a=a-b
a*=b;   //a=a*b
a/=b;   //a=a/b

Increment Operator (++):-value increased by one

a++;    //a=a+1

Decrement Operator (--):-value decreased by one

a--:    //a=a-1

Logical Operator:-If you want to combine two or more conditions then you can use logical operators.

AND     &&    (double ampersand) 
OR      ||     (pipe)
NOT     !

Ternary Operator (?):-alternative of if-else

syntax:- (condition)?("expression1");("expression2");

